Talia provides customized financial planning and wealth building strategies for SIG clients and their families. She brings experience in philanthropic planning from her years in development at the School of Engineering at Stanford University. She later co-founded SearchFox (acquired by Yahoo) and joined Stanford Investment Group in 2005. Her passion for philanthropy and expertise in equity compensation/liquidity event planning empowers clients to make financial decisions that are both wise and personally meaningful.





